title: Table, Pembroke, late 18th century
medium: Mahogany inlaid wih satinwood and rosewood
signed: Incised signature on inside surface of top: Samuel...
creditline: Bequest of Mrs. John Innes Kane
description:
In the style of George Hepplewhite, died 1786.
Oval top, veneer on maple; leaves at ends hinged and supported by hinged wooden brackets.  Frieze, veneered on pine, contains a single drawer with bowed front,  a dummy drawer in opposite face.  Legs square and tapering, with brass casters; line inlay of satinwood on legs, frieze and top; cross-banding of rosewood in frieze and top.
